	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=69206><span id= >dimle</span></a><br><span id=notbold>50 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.58]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I'm sure I will get some disagreement, but for my two cents, I just don't think having a variety of weapon skills matters much to a bard.&nbsp;&nbsp;You are not going to be a primary melee damage dealer much beyond level 30 anyway, but will really be useful for your songs.  For my bard, I just worked on 1HS only, and I never really felt like I was missing out on anything.<br><br>Maybe if someone just dropped a piercer on me tomorrow, and I couldnt' use it, I would feel differently, but for me, I'm not going to slow down my leveling to work a skill that is really just a luxury to my class, anyway.  If I can dish good damage with 1HS, I don't see the point in maxing other skills.  For a warrior, sure, because their melee skill is almost as important to them as their HPs, and being able to swap weapons based on the situation is useful, but for us bards I don't see it.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></td></tr>
