	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [4.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Torin's Horn seems to be bugged. No skill ups and no instrument damage boost that I can see.&nbsp;&nbsp;Others have reported similar problems with it in EQDiva.  There is rumor that it may be involved in a quest in Shar Val but I have not seen this confirmed.  I plan to investigate if further soon.<br><br>A store bought horn is good enough for practicing. What I did was take the horn and go to East Karana at the High Hold zone.  Instead of following the trail down into the plains I went off the the left (south) up onto the cliff wall.  I equipped the horn and started playing DDD song. Then I went AFK for a couple of hours.  Skilled up just fine and you are far enough away from the zone to avoid any trains.<br><br>I suggest a Combine Horn from Katta Castellum bard vendor. The Combine instruments all seem to be about 18-20% better than store bought. For example, Combine Drums are very close in performance to Mistmoore Drums and only cost me 58pp. Combine Mandolin increases Hymn regen rates for me by 2 hp/tick. I have not yet tried a Combine Horn. My guess is that the boost is along the same lines.  Anyway, the price is right. You just need to get to Katta.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
