	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=102398844130360>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102398844130360>RE: questions</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102398844130360#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Jun 13th 1:22 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.15]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I can address item 3 but I will leave 1 and 2 to more advanced bards than myself.&nbsp;&nbsp;Although I know some bard songs will stack with effects (Haste for example) so you can have 1 spell, 1 item effect, and a bard song in many cases.  Some bard songs will stack with other songs and have a cumulative effect, too.<br><br>Question 3:<br><br>Bard = Carpal Tunnel Syndrome.  Macros are not the way to twist.  Since you can fail to start a song regardless of your skill with the instrument/voice all you need is one failed start to throw the whole sequence in the crapper.  What I did is make hot keys for just one song and then use the number keys: tap 1 - start first song, tap 2 twice to stop first song and start second. Tap 3 twice to stop second and start the third. Tap 1 twice to stop third and start first song again.  Repeat sequence until cramps begin.<br><br>The nice thing is that when cramps start you just kick on Selo's Accelerando and hit the Num Lock key. Run until you're stretched again.  Then go back and start all over.<br><br>I hope this helps.<br><br>Bards, it is said, are the 3rd best solo class in the game after Necromancers and Druids.  Honestly, I think the only thing Druids have over bards it the porting thing.  I keep a /say Meep! Meep! hot key for when I run past them in the plains of Karana.<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Thu Jun 13 13:15:18 2002</em></p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
