	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=135979><span id=Scholar>RavinRed</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>75 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I have twisted 4 songs successfully.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, hot keys, rested wrists, and no lag are about required, and you'd better not be changing out instruments or having to do ANYTHING else but stand there and play/sing!  A suggestion to eliminate some lag - turn your back on the action.  This won't work if you're targeting the mob, but if you're just buffing the melee group it can speed up your ability to twist.<br><br>Calthine Faeriesong<br>Bard of the 37th Song<br>Torture Guild<br>Vazelle<br></p>&nbsp;<br><a href=HTTP://calthine.tripod.com target=_new>Calthine Faeriesong</a><br>53 Minstrel <br>Vazelle</td></td></tr>
