	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes.html?class=4&mid=102260195681176>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102260195681176>RE: Twisting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=102260195681176#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, May 28th 12:16 PM 2002</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1056 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.65]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>The easier way to twist is not to use the mouse.&nbsp;&nbsp;I set up hot keys for my common used songs and then type the number on the top row of my keyboard that goes with the slot # holding the song I want to play.  Alternatively, you can hold down the alt key and press the number of the spell slot holding your mem'd song.  Tap the number key to start the song.  Tap the number key of the second song twice (first time stops song 1, second time starts next song) I do 3 songs this way easily.<br><br>To do 4 or 5 songs you need a fast, reliable internet connection with no lag, well stretched fingers, a good sense of timing, and no signs of carpal tunnel syndrome.  Most bards, I am told, cannot do 5 songs.  A lot depends on the duration of the songs you want to twist, also.<br><br>I have done a 4 song twist before but more often than not, even with my excellent internet connection and manual dexterity (I am a guitar player p/t in RL) I find I miss the 4th song (song 1 drops before I can get song 4 started).  A 4 song twist is very tiring to maintain for any extended period.  Additionally, I spend so much time concentrating on the timing and sequence that I find I cannot enjoy the game.  So, I only do 3 song twists when I am grouped and not in melee and 2 songs or even 1 if I am in melee. Solo I often do 3 songs while meleeing but prefer to do 2 where I can.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></td></tr>
